IForecaster<java.lang.Double>
public class NaiveForecaster
extends AbstractRForecaster

This is one of the forecasters used in the research paper on Self-adaptive workload classification and forecasting for proactive resource provisioning (http://dx.doi.org/10.1002/cpe.3224), authored by Herbst et al.

Since:
1.10
Author:
Nikolas Herbst The na√Øve forecast considers only the value of the most recent observation assuming that this value has the highest probability for the next forecast point. Horizon: very short term forecast (1-2 points) Overhead: nearly none O(1)
